              <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="BS" typeId="b539-c71b-9239-8da0">2 (3)</characteristic>
                <characteristic name="F" typeId="84f1-6495-b3c8-6025">10</characteristic>
                <characteristic name="S" typeId="38b6-8429-f0fd-11cb">10</characteristic>
                <characteristic name="R" typeId="10a0-8c50-f9d5-466b">10</characteristic>
              </characteristics>
            </profile>
            <profile name="Sensor Array" typeId="456a-26d9-cb27-bd5c" typeName="Wargear" hidden="false" id="edc2-985c-2c3a-c380">
              <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Description" typeId="9e5e-2cfd-7c93-749a">If enemy infiltrators set up within 4D6&quot; of the tower then the tower may take a &apos;free&apos; shot at them with its Markerlight (or sound the alarm in the raid scenario). If the Markerlight hits, then a Seeker missile can immediately be launcher. These shots are taken before the battle begins and may cause infiltrators to fall back.</characteristic>
              </characteristics>
            </profile>
          </profiles>
        </selectionEntry>
      </selectionEntries>
      <modifiers>
        <modifier type="set" value="true" field="hidden">
          <conditions>
            <condition type="lessThan" value="1" field="selections" scope="force" childId="ffb5-655b-9721-de5f" shared="true" id="73f0-56a4-e2a2-f491" includeChildSelections="true" childName="Show Forgeworld"/>
          </conditions>
        </modifier>
      </modifiers>
      <profiles>
        <profile name="Immobile" typeId="ccb3-7790-3139-7975" typeName="Abilities" hidden="false" id="df56-3d49-6220-332c">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Description" typeId="e24a-6018-20cf-d76c">A Remote Sensor Tower cannot move once it has entered the battle, and counts in all respects as a vehicle that has suffered an Immobilised damage result (which cannot be repaired)</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Damage" typeId="ccb3-7790-3139-7975" typeName="Abilities" hidden="false" id="2197-18ad-cb51-6b7e">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Description" typeId="e24a-6018-20cf-d76c">If the tower takes a Crew Shaken or Crew Stunned result (and therefore not fire), then it cannot use its Markerlight, Target Lock or Sensor Array.

If the turret takes an Immobilised damage result, then it has no effect, but the turret still counts as damaged for the purposes of calculating Victory Points</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Victory Pts" typeId="ccb3-7790-3139-7975" typeName="Abilities" hidden="false" id="de71-f087-cfb0-a69c">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Description" typeId="e24a-6018-20cf-d76c">Remote sensor towers may not claim Victory Points for occupying table quarters or other objectives.</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Target Lock (Remote Sensor Tower)" typeId="ccb3-7790-3139-7975" typeName="Abilities" hidden="false" id="bfec-3832-49cb-ef1a">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Description" typeId="e24a-6018-20cf-d76c">At the start of the Tau player&apos;s Shooting phase choose a single Tau vehicle on the table, and it counts as having the Target Lock upgrade for that turn&apos;s firing only.</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <constraints>
        <constraint type="max" value="1" field="selections" scope="parent" shared="true" id="985b-751b-d59a-5791"/>
      </constraints>
    </selectionEntry>
